-- China Stock Market Declines are Correction, Not Ceiling, CICC's Hao Says
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-28T01:08:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-28/china-stock-market-declines-are-correction-not-ceiling-cicc-s-hao-says.html
The recent decline in China’s stocks
is a correction rather than a ceiling for the nation’s benchmark
index, according to China International Capital Corp. The
Shanghai Composite Index had dropped four out of the past five
days after the central bank raised interest rates.  The Federal Reserve’s possible asset-purchase program bodes
well for emerging-market equities, Hao Hong, CICC’s Beijing-
based global equity strategist, wrote in a note to clients.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Allen Wan at 
 awan3@bloomberg.net  